üöÄ Quick Deploy Options

Option 1: Render (Recommended - Free & Easy)
Push your code to GitHub first
Go to render.com
Sign up with GitHub ‚Üí "New +" ‚Üí "Web Service"
Connect your repo with these settings:
Build Command: pip install -r requirements.txt
Start Command: gunicorn app:app

Option 2: Railway (Also Free)
Go to railway.app
"Deploy from GitHub repo" ‚Üí select your repository
Auto-deploys instantly!

Option 3: Heroku (Classic option)
heroku.com ‚Üí Create app
Connect GitHub repo or use CLI

üìÅ Files I Created for Deployment
requirements.txt - Python dependencies
Procfile - Tells hosting service how to run your app
runtime.txt - Specifies Python version
.gitignore - Excludes unnecessary files
README.md - Deployment instructions

üîß Production Changes Made
Added environment variable support for secret key
Configured proper host/port binding
Disabled debug mode for production
Set up gunicorn as production server

